kdb_mcp_demo.py

Runs the dynamic KDB MCP server using a **mock KDB connection** so you can
test and explore the tool generation without a live KDB+/Q process.

Usage:
python kdb_mcp_demo.py          # stdio transport (Claude Desktop)
python kdb_mcp_demo.py –sse    # SSE transport  (HTTP / inspect)

The mock exposes these sample KDB functions:
getTrades(sym, n)   – last N trades for a symbol
getVWAP(sym, date)  – volume-weighted average price
getOHLCV(sym, date) – OHLCV bar for a symbol/date
listSymbols()       – all available symbols
getPortfolio()      – current portfolio positions
